On november 2, 2013
[4364081]

In the vein of Three-Trooper Tourney, I propose a new championship... which takes MiniTroopers to its utmost essence.

ONE-MAN ARMY

Rules

1. Your army may have one, and only one, trooper. Be sure to protect your army with a password so it stays that way!

2. To join, make your army name into a link, followed by your Army Name and player name in ordinary text so that participants know who to challenge. Place this link at the bottom of the list of armies.

Example: http://bimotivality.minitroopers.com/hq Bimotivality / SoItBegins

3. To move up the rank list, beat the person above you (using 'Infiltrate!' in the Pick a Fight section) and post the replay with the updated list.
It is possible to not realize you weren't at the last page, and use an old version of the list. If this happens, please edit your post to fix it!

4. You can have up to two armies per player in the list. You don't fight your own army— you skip over them.

5a. If you want to replace one of your two armies with another, put [RETIRED] next to your retiring army in the list— also, strikethrough the link.

Example: http://bimotivality.minitroopers.com/hq [RETIRED]
Then, you can add your new army at the bottom of the list.

5b. If you want to take a vacation, mark your army [INACTIVE], in the same way. People can skip over INACTIVE armies.

6a. Pilots with a Light Tank or Helicopter are prohibited.

6b. Special rules for vehicle users:
If you attack another army, and your Tank or Helicopter deploys, the match is forfeit.
If you attack another army, and the other guy has a Tank/Helicopter and you win somehow (on foot), it's a justly deserved victory!

7. Have fun!

[8640217]

by the way, i just noticed that the army in position number 21: sub2dawnblade / xtremekiwi has 6 troopers. you are suppose to only have 1 trooper. This one man army ladder has been going on for months HOW IS IT THAT IM THE ONLY ONE WHO NOTICED THIS?!?

Im guessing that this USED to be a 1 man army, by looking at all the low level troopers and the 1 high level trooper. Since this army was not password protected, someone may have hijacked that army and bought 5 extra troopers just to get this army disqualified from the belt. I feel bad for the original owner, but the rules are the rules.
This has happened to me before. I use minibootters to train my 80+ recruits and, on a few of them, some idiot accessed one of my 80+ recruits and bought an extra trooper or 2. I can't remember which of those 80+ recruits it was. I'd have to go back and check when i have free time. Im glad i protect gadget57 with a password.

45424

6b. Special rules for vehicle users:
If you attack another army, and your Tank or Helicopter deploys, the match is forfeit.
If you attack another army, and the other guy has a Tank/Helicopter and you win somehow (on foot), it's a justly deserved victory!

You still need to beat testmiep no matter it has a tank or not.

[8640217]

If you guys are wondering why tanks are forbidden from one man army, here is your answer
http://spiral-team.minitroopers.com/b...

As you can see, the tank wiped out half of my team really quickly but my troopers were lucky and brought down the tank. So it took 2 rockets to bring down this tank and the trooper inside it is still alive and he kills my team.
I think only tanks should be banned and not helicopters because helicopters are easier to take down than tanks. The helicopter can easily be brought down with 1 rocket and when the helicopter go down the trooper inside the helicopter dies too. I see this happen during raids because some of my recruits have helicopter and their helicopter get destroyed with a single rocket, but the trooper in the tank will not die with the tank so you have to use up more resources and ammunition to bring down the tank than the helicopter and the tank can use both rocket and machine gun and the helicopter uses only machine gun.
Also one more thing the tanks rockets cannot be dodged even with the dodger ability because my soldier with the m1 bazooka had dodger and he still got hit by the tank but helicopter shots can be dodged with dodger and tuck an roll. I dont know if this is on purpose or if this is a glitch or something but

So you should ban the tanks but not the helicopters, the tanks are more overpowered.

If you guys are wondering why tanks are forbidden from one man army, here is your answer
http://spiral-team.minitroopers.com/b...

As you can see, the tank wiped out half of my team really quickly but my troopers were lucky and brought down the tank. So it took 2 rockets to bring down this tank and the trooper inside it is still alive and he kills my team.
I think only tanks should be banned and not helicopters because helicopters are easier to take down than tanks. The helicopter can easily be brought down with 1 rocket and when the helicopter go down the trooper inside the helicopter dies too. I see this happen during raids because some of my recruits have helicopter and their helicopter get destroyed with a single rocket, but the trooper in the tank will not die with the tank so you have to use up more resources and ammunition to bring down the tank than the helicopter and the tank can use both rocket and machine gun and the helicopter uses only machine gun.
Also one more thing the tanks rockets cannot be dodged even with the dodger ability because my soldier with the m1 bazooka had dodger and he still got hit by the tank but helicopter shots can be dodged with dodger and tuck an roll. I dont know if this is on purpose or if this is a glitch or something but

So you should ban the tanks but not the helicopters, the tanks are more overpowered.
